svgl is a library that displays SVG documents using OpenGL.
http://svgl.sf.net

authors:
Stephane Conversy, conversy@enac.fr, http://www.tls.cena.fr/~conversy
Jean-Daniel Fekete, fekete@inria.fr, http://www.lri.fr/~conversy
copyright (c) 2000-2004

license: gnu LGPL
see licence.txt
see docs/agglicense.txt for agg license

build:
you must have built glft, available at the same place than svgl (install not mandatory)
mkdir ~/build/svgl
cd ~/build/svgl
~/src/svgl/build/automake/bootstrap
./configure
(if glft is not installed, try env PKG_CONFIG_PATH=$HOME/build/glft ./configure, assuming that glft has been built in ~/build/glft)
make

test:
env GLFT_FONTDIR=/my/path/to/truetype/fonts demos/00simple

install:
make install

(see docs/INSTALL for further explanations)


documentation:
see docs/*

part of svgl was developed during SC's post-doc period at
the Ecole des Mines de Nantes (http://www.emn.fr)
from October 2000 to September 2001.

Stephane Conversy is now at Ecole Nationale de l'Aviation Civile
and Centre d'Etudes de la Navigation Aerienne, Toulouse, France

Jean-Daniel Fekete is now at the
Laboratoire de Recherche en Informatique,
Universite Paris-Sud an INRIA, Orsay, France

